Program: Free Thinking
Title: Therapy Versus Prayer
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b03g2yj3
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 8 Nov 2013
Is the idea of counselling as non-judgmental listening flawed? Christopher Harding from Edinburgh University focuses his talk on attitudes in Japan and the UK. He asks whether prayer involves fewer hidden pressures than a session with a shrink. Producer: Fiona McLean.